Role: You are a Senior UI/UX Designer and Design Systems Architect specialized in complex Enterprise Resource Planning (ERP) and professional SaaS platforms.

Task: Design a comprehensive UI/UX framework and detailed page wireframes for a professional web application based on the following inputs:

1. Project Foundation
App Name/Niche: Alpha Zero
Primary User Roles: @UserRoles

Key User Stories: @UserStories

2. Visual Identity & Design System
Create a robust Design System that supports Light and Dark modes. Please define:

Color Palette: @DesignAssets/ColorPalettes

Typography: A scale for Headings (H1-H6) and Body text (Small, Regular, Large). Recommend a font pairing that supports both Latin (English) and Arabic scripts seamlessly (e.g., IBM Plex Sans & IBM Plex Sans Arabic).

Spacing & Grid: Define a 4px or 8px base spacing system for a high-density "professional" layout.

3. Internationalization (i18n) Strategy
Describe how the UI adapts between English (LTR) and Arabic (RTL). Address:

Mirroring logic for navigation bars and sidebars.

Iconography handling (which icons flip and which stay static).

Alignment rules for data tables and form labels.

4. Detailed Page Architecture
For each of the following pages: [List your pages here, e.g., Dashboard, Analytics Report, User Management], provide:

Information Architecture: A bulleted list of every data point, button, and filter required.

Layout Structure: Describe the placement of elements (e.g., "Left-aligned sticky sidebar, top global search, center-fluid data grid").

UX Logic: How does the page handle "Empty States," "Loading States," and "Error States"?

Complexity Management: Since this is a complicated app, explain how you use progressive disclosure (e.g., accordions, modals, or slide-overs) to keep the UI clean.

Output Format: Please use Markdown for the Design System tables and structured headings for the page descriptions.